data.description: Step into your dream home where luxury meets nature! Imagine a picturesque oasis awaiting your personal touch – and now, it's yours with a generous $3,000 landscaping allowance. Transform your outdoor space into a haven of tranquility, surrounded by lush greenery and vibrant blooms. Whether you envision a cozy garden retreat or a stylish entertainment area, this allowance empowers you to customize your surroundings to match your lifestyle. Picture hosting gatherings on your beautiful deck surrounded by towering trees or enjoying peaceful evenings in your own private hot tub sanctuary. This is more than a house; it's an opportunity to create the perfect backdrop for a life well-lived. Seize the chance to make your mark and turn this house into your personalized haven with the $3,000 landscaping allowance – because your dream home deserves a dream setting. Beautiful and remodeled traditional home in Northwest Forsyth on 2+ wooded acres teeming with nature and wildlife. This home exudes country charm with a rocking chair front porch on a quiet road. Walking in the front door, guests will see the updated staircase with black hardwood steps and iron ballisters. The family room boasts a grand fireplace and has a new coat of black paint amidst the newly painted white walls. There is ample space in the family room for a sectional and large wall-mounted TV. The open kitchen is adjacent to the family room with new appliances, and on-trend butcher block countertops that flank the new black cabinetry with upgraded gold hardware. The kitchen sink is a new, deep farmhouse-style sink set against a window that looks out over the expanse of woods. The breakfast area is large enough for a sizeable dining table adjacent to the new sliding glass doors leading onto the deck with a large new jacuzzi.  New Samsung oversized washer and dryer to remain. New flooring on the main level with tile in the kitchen and new carpet in the master on the main. The second floor boasts two oversized bedrooms with dormer windows facing the front yard letting in natural light. Each bedroom contains walk-in closets with art-deco faux brick accent walls. The guest bath has been completely remodeled with designer touches. The second-floor hall has new black tile leading to the bedrooms containing new carpet. The terrace level contains two huge areas, one side finished which can be used as extra bedrooms, living space, or recreation. The unfinished side provides ample storage with new sliding glass doors. All new lighting fixtures on the main and upper levels. This property is quiet, country living in the Matt community with top-rated schools.
